I would recommend to go through the page outline, traversing the hierarchy using `PdfOutline`&#39;s children in order to traverse them recursively.

To find the page number by a page object, you should use `pdfDocument.getPageNumber(PdfDictionary).`

The method walking through the outlines may look as following:

    void walkOutlines(PdfOutline outline, Map&lt;String, PdfObject&gt; names, PdfDocument pdfDocument) 
    {
        if (outline.getDestination() != null) 
        {
            System.out.println(outline.getTitle() + &quot;: page &quot; +
                    pdfDocument.getPageNumber((PdfDictionary) outline.getDestination().getDestinationPage(names)));
        }
        for (PdfOutline child : outline.getAllChildren()) 
        {
            walkOutlines(child, names, pdfDocument);
        }
    }

The main entry point where you call the method to traverse the root: 

    PdfNameTree destsTree = pdfDoc.getCatalog().getNameTree(PdfName.Dests);
    PdfOutline root = pdfDoc.getOutlines(false);
    walkOutlines(root, destsTree.getNames(), pdfDoc);

